From Wednesday, motorists will have to dig deeper into their pockets with a petrol price increase of 49 cents per litre. JOHANNESBURG The South African National Consumer Union says it is just the beginning of the tough times consumers are facing in light of the petrol price hike.From Wednesday, motorists will have to dig deeper into their pockets with a petrol price increase of 49 cents per litre.Diesel has also increased by between 30 and 32 cents per litre.The union's Ina Wilken says the fuel levy increase in April also affects the spending patterns of consumers. I predict that we will have more increases in view of the fact of the state of our economy, and that we might become a total junk state. It s very bad news for consumers, they have got to tighten their belts once again and even more so in future. 